metatags.abstract: As an epileptic, we all know what would trigger my seizures may or may not apply to you, so keep this in mind as you read on. I would also like to say that, though I'm an epileptic, I'm not on any AEDs nor any other prescribed drugs, and had only taken Phenobarbital for an extremely short time in early childhood due to tonic-clonic events.

metatags.og:description: Kimtech™ is your partner in driving progress. As part of Kimberly Clark's 150-year-old legacy of innovation and partnership with the scientific community, we're proud to offer Kimtech™ Purple Nitrile Exam Gloves. These purple nitrile gloves guard against incidental splashes, are made of a highly durable nitrile polymer and are powder free and not made with natural rubber latex (some say “latex free"). The ambidextrous gloves are available in 9.5" and 12" (Nitrile-Xtra™) lengths, are available in various sizes and have a beaded cuff for easy donning. Your workers will enjoy excellent dexterity and tactile sensitivity, thanks to the textured fingertips. They are even cleared for use in chemotherapy. When users see the distinctive purple color, they can have confidence in their own protection. These purple nitrile exam gloves can be diverted from the landfill through The RightCycle™ Program by Kimberly-Clark Professional™.
